http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/CM-special-address-on-National-Youth-Day/article13993797.ece

Chief Minister N. Chandrababu Naidu will deliver a special address on the National Youth Day on the occasion of the birth anniversary of Swami Vivekananda on Tuesday at Andhra University Convocation Hall.The programme is being organised by the Ramakrishna Mission.Spreading the messageAccording to Swami Atmavidananda, secretary of RK Mission, the spiritual organisation has been celebrating the birth anniversary of Swami Vivekananda to spread his message among the youth and create awareness among the young minds in the city. About 3,000 students are expected to attend the celebrations.The programme will begin at 7.30 a.m. with a cultural programme by the students, Vedic chanting, and Swadesha Mantra.While the welcome address will be delivered by secretary of the mission, Dr. Subrahmanymam, former principal of Vivekananda College, Tamil Nadu, will deliver the inaugural address.The programme being organised by RK Mission is to mark the birth anniversary of Swami Vivekananda